          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "This now tells users to create schema_version 5 metadata with `status: planned`, but v5 metadata is identity-only and rejects `status` as a legacy field. Following this instruction produces invalid metadata instead of a valid plan-only track; status needs to be derived from `impl-plan.json` rather than written in `metadata.json`.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": ".claude/commands/track/plan-only.md",
              "line": 17,
              "category": "factual_error"
            },
            {
              "message": "This check still describes `status: planned` as part of the planning-only metadata condition even though schema_version 5 no longer stores `status`; v5 planning status is derived. As written, the activation instructions ask reviewers to confirm a field that valid v5 metadata must not contain.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": ".claude/commands/track/activate.md",
              "line": 13,
              "category": "factual_error"
            }
