        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "Python is not actually optional here: `cargo make` wrappers such as `guides-*`, `conventions-*`, and `architecture-rules-*` invoke `python3` on the host, so those documented tasks will fail on a machine without host Python even if `scripts/` is never run manually.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "LOCAL_DEVELOPMENT.md",
              "line": 10,
              "category": "factual error"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:640b1c2030ad5064ade5d2127be39458bd65d615e63828ee8d90997793fff2cd",
          "at": "2026-04-27T13:32:47Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "Host requirements now imply Python is only needed for `scripts/` helpers, but several documented `cargo make` tasks (`guides-*`, `conventions-*`, `architecture-rules-*`) still invoke `python3` directly on the host, so users without host Python cannot run them.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "LOCAL_DEVELOPMENT.md",
              "line": 10,
              "category": "factual error"
            },
            {
              "message": "The tools-daemon note says `ci` / `deny` / `verify-*` remain `run --rm`, but `cargo make verify-latest-track` is a host task that calls `cargo make --allow-private verify-latest-track-local` directly, so this statement is false for at least one `verify-*` gate.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "LOCAL_DEVELOPMENT.md",
              "line": 38,
              "category": "factual error"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:640b1c2030ad5064ade5d2127be39458bd65d615e63828ee8d90997793fff2cd",
          "at": "2026-04-27T13:34:23Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "This says host-side verification is run via `cargo make verify-*`, but most `verify-*` tasks are actually docker-compose wrappers in `Makefile.toml` (`verify-arch-docs`, `verify-track-registry`, `verify-orchestra`, etc.); only `verify-latest-track` runs directly on the host. The wording will mislead readers about where the verification family executes.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "LOCAL_DEVELOPMENT.md",
              "line": 13,
              "category": "factual error"
            }
          ],
